<strong>Time:</strong> 15:15 ‚Äî 16:30<br />
<strong>Title:</strong> Efficient hedging under ambiguity <br />
<strong>Abstract:</strong> It is well known that the minimal superhedging price of a contingent claim is typically too high for the seller in practice. In a non-dominated model uncertainty framework, we propose alternative hedging criteria and, based on an aggregation result and new findings on representation of convex functionals, we derive existence of optimal strategies and dual representation of minimal prices.</dd>
